{"body": "I think we should keep `bundle exec` on our guides yes, because it's the safe way of executing the commands without relying on bins / paths, and different setups. It may differ if you're under a mac, linux ubuntu, fedora, windows, so we can try to avoid that by letting `bundle exec` as a recommendation. If the developer knows about his system, he knows if he should use it or not I think.\n\nCan you please remove the `bundle exec` changes, and squash your commits? Thanks.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6823244", "created_at": "2012-07-07T13:57:15Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6998#issuecomment-6823244", "updated_at": "2012-07-07T13:57:15Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6998, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523e131cbd354364b900d151"}, "id": 6823244, "issue_url": "h